                            <comment id="14530672" author="jking3" created="Wed, 6 May 2015 15:01:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt; I added these tests, so I caused the issue.&lt;br/&gt;
But I have some issues with the fix:&lt;br/&gt;
1. The CI build failed - why was this merged?&lt;br/&gt;
2. The fix only addresses CMake.  Was it not necessary to update autoconf?&lt;br/&gt;
3. I think it would have been better to use CMake and autoconf to detect the presence of librt and include it as a platform dependency instead of putting it into the lib/cpp/test makefile.  librt is required on linux when you use boost::thread.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14530677" author="jking3" created="Wed, 6 May 2015 15:03:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also this points out that the Travis CI environment is not currently giving us MacOSX validation.  Can it do that?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14530701" author="tbartelmess" created="Wed, 6 May 2015 15:21:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You are right. I forgot about autoconf, I only tested with CMake :/. Unfortunately I am not able to fix this until tomorrow evening.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If no one else has fixed it until then I&apos;ll submit a new patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sorry&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14530706" author="tbartelmess" created="Wed, 6 May 2015 15:22:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://docs.travis-ci.com/user/multi-os/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://docs.travis-ci.com/user/multi-os/&lt;/a&gt; They have a multi OS beta, so hopefully we can add this soon&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14530773" author="jking3" created="Wed, 6 May 2015 15:55:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think that you can use &quot;if (UNIX AND NOT APPLE)&quot; in the cmake patch, and you can ignore item #3 in my list above.  Only two of the tests need -lrt, no need to link anything else against it.  Just need the autoconf environment fix.  Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
